{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":944,"text":"When I was 14 years old,\nI was interested in science --"},{"time":5339,"text":"fascinated by it,\nexcited to learn about it."},{"time":8479,"text":"And I had a high school science teacher\nwho would say to the class,"},{"time":12562,"text":"\"The girls don't have to listen to this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":16800,"text":"Encouraging, yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18229,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":19340,"text":"I chose not to listen --\nbut to that statement alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24710,"text":"So let me take you\nto the Andes mountains in Chile,"},{"time":28441,"text":"500 kilometers, 300 miles\nnortheast of Santiago."},{"time":33284,"text":"It's very remote, it's very dry\nand it's very beautiful."},{"time":38087,"text":"And there's not much there."},{"time":39486,"text":"There are condors, there are tarantulas,"},{"time":42150,"text":"and at night, when the light dims,"},{"time":44671,"text":"it reveals one of the darkest\nskies on Earth."},{"time":48906,"text":"It's kind of a magic place, the mountain."},{"time":51480,"text":"It's a wonderful combination\nof very remote mountaintop"},{"time":55841,"text":"with exquisitely sophisticated technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59508,"text":"And our ancestors, for as long\nas there's been recorded history,"},{"time":63124,"text":"have looked at the night sky\nand pondered the nature of our existence."},{"time":68506,"text":"And we're no exception, our generation."},{"time":71536,"text":"The only difficulty is\nthat the night sky now is blocked"},{"time":74656,"text":"by the glare of city lights."},{"time":77058,"text":"And so astronomers go\nto these very remote mountaintops"},{"time":80696,"text":"to view and to study the cosmos."},{"time":82981,"text":"So telescopes\nare our window to the cosmos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88042,"text":"It's no exaggeration to say that\nthe Southern Hemisphere is going to be"},{"time":92089,"text":"the future of astronomy\nfor the 21st century."},{"time":96135,"text":"We have an array\nof existing telescopes already,"},{"time":99391,"text":"in the Andes mountains in Chile,"},{"time":101447,"text":"and that's soon to be joined by a really\nsensational array of new capability."},{"time":106608,"text":"There will be two international groups\nthat are going to be building"},{"time":109831,"text":"giant telescopes, sensitive\nto optical radiation, as our eyes are."},{"time":115669,"text":"There will be a survey telescope"},{"time":117564,"text":"that will be scanning the sky\nevery few nights."},{"time":121366,"text":"There will be radio telescopes,"},{"time":122916,"text":"sensitive to long-wavelength\nradio radiation."},{"time":126448,"text":"And then there will be\ntelescopes in space."},{"time":129587,"text":"There'll be a successor\nto the Hubble Space Telescope;"},{"time":132508,"text":"it's called the James Webb Telescope,"},{"time":134569,"text":"and it will be launched in 2018."},{"time":137078,"text":"There'll be a satellite called TESS"},{"time":138808,"text":"that will discover planets\noutside of our solar system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144259,"text":"For the last decade,\nI've been leading a group --"},{"time":146913,"text":"a consortium -- international group,"},{"time":149154,"text":"to build what will be, when it's finished,"},{"time":152161,"text":"the largest optical\ntelescope in existence."},{"time":155489,"text":"It's called the Giant\nMagellan Telescope, or GMT."},{"time":159748,"text":"This telescope is going to have mirrors\nthat are 8.4 meters in diameter --"},{"time":164505,"text":"each of the mirrors."},{"time":165691,"text":"That's almost 27 feet."},{"time":167354,"text":"So it dwarfs this stage -- maybe\nout to the fourth row in this audience."},{"time":171850,"text":"Each of the seven mirrors\nin this telescope"},{"time":174898,"text":"will be almost 27 feet in diameter."},{"time":178706,"text":"Together, the seven mirrors\nin this telescope will comprise"},{"time":182658,"text":"80 feet in diameter."},{"time":184723,"text":"So, essentially the size\nof this entire auditorium."},{"time":188448,"text":"The whole telescope will stand\nabout 43 meters high,"},{"time":192118,"text":"and again, being in Rio,"},{"time":194832,"text":"some of you have been to see\nthe statue of the giant Christ."},{"time":198475,"text":"The scale is comparable in height;"},{"time":200328,"text":"in fact, it's smaller\nthan this telescope will be."},{"time":204192,"text":"It's comparable to the size\nof the Statue of Liberty."},{"time":207721,"text":"And it's going to be housed\nin an enclosure that's 22 stories --"},{"time":211794,"text":"60 meters high."},{"time":213717,"text":"But it's an unusual building\nto protect this telescope."},{"time":216743,"text":"It will have open windows to the sky,"},{"time":218553,"text":"be able to point and look at the sky,"},{"time":220925,"text":"and it will actually rotate on a base --"},{"time":223577,"text":"2,000 tons of rotating building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227719,"text":"The Giant Magellan Telescope\nwill have 10 times the resolution"},{"time":232576,"text":"of the Hubble Space Telescope."},{"time":234934,"text":"It will be 20 million times\nmore sensitive than the human eye."},{"time":239593,"text":"And it may, for the first time ever,\nbe capable of finding life on planets"},{"time":245753,"text":"outside of our solar system."},{"time":248469,"text":"It's going to allow us to look back\nat the first light in the universe --"},{"time":252866,"text":"literally, the dawn of the cosmos."},{"time":255257,"text":"The cosmic dawn."},{"time":257763,"text":"It's a telescope that's\ngoing to allow us to peer back,"},{"time":261541,"text":"witness galaxies as they were\nwhen they were actually assembling,"},{"time":265350,"text":"the first black holes in the universe,\nthe first galaxies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269690,"text":"Now, for thousands of years,\nwe have been studying the cosmos,"},{"time":274322,"text":"we've been wondering\nabout our place in the universe."},{"time":277000,"text":"The ancient Greeks told us"},{"time":278689,"text":"that the Earth was the center\nof the universe."},{"time":281195,"text":"Five hundred years ago,\nCopernicus displaced the Earth,"},{"time":284845,"text":"and put the Sun\nat the heart of the cosmos."},{"time":288785,"text":"And as we've learned over the centuries,"},{"time":290863,"text":"since Galileo Galilei,\nthe Italian scientist,"},{"time":293605,"text":"first turned, in that time, a two-inch,\nvery small telescope, to the sky,"},{"time":298879,"text":"every time we have built\nlarger telescopes,"},{"time":301918,"text":"we have learned something\nabout the universe;"},{"time":304141,"text":"we've made discoveries, without exception."},{"time":308908,"text":"We've learned in the 20th century\nthat the universe is expanding"},{"time":312669,"text":"and that our own solar system\nis not at the center of that expansion."},{"time":317757,"text":"We know now that the universe\nis made of about 100 billion galaxies"},{"time":323060,"text":"that are visible to us,"},{"time":324734,"text":"and each one of those galaxies\nhas 100 billion stars within it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331234,"text":"So we're looking now\nat the deepest image of the cosmos"},{"time":334120,"text":"that's ever been taken."},{"time":336015,"text":"It was taken using\nthe Hubble Space Telescope,"},{"time":338857,"text":"and by pointing the telescope at what\nwas previously a blank region of sky,"},{"time":343771,"text":"before the launch of Hubble."},{"time":345394,"text":"And if you can imagine this tiny area,"},{"time":347681,"text":"it's only one-fiftieth\nof the size of the full moon."},{"time":351035,"text":"So, if you can imagine the full moon."},{"time":353099,"text":"And there are now 10,000 galaxies\nvisible within that image."},{"time":357782,"text":"And the faintness of those images\nand the tiny size is only a result"},{"time":362484,"text":"of the fact that those galaxies\nare so far away, the vast distances."},{"time":366915,"text":"And each of those galaxies\nmay contain within it"},{"time":369872,"text":"a few billion or even hundreds\nof billions of individual stars."},{"time":375591,"text":"Telescopes are like time machines."},{"time":377634,"text":"So the farther back we look in space,\nthe further back we see in time."},{"time":382470,"text":"And they're like light buckets --\nliterally, they collect light."},{"time":385680,"text":"So larger the bucket,\nthe larger the mirror we have,"},{"time":388938,"text":"the more light we can see,\nand the farther back we can view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393610,"text":"So, we've learned in the last century"},{"time":395905,"text":"that there are exotic objects\nin the universe -- black holes."},{"time":398863,"text":"We've even learned\nthat there's dark matter and dark energy"},{"time":401664,"text":"that we can't see."},{"time":403218,"text":"So you're looking now\nat an actual image of dark matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407974,"text":"You got it. Not all audiences get that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410641,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412430,"text":"So the way we infer\nthe presence of dark matter --"},{"time":415178,"text":"we can't see it -- but there's\nan unmistakable tug, due to gravity."},{"time":421302,"text":"We now can look out,\nwe see this sea of galaxies"},{"time":424704,"text":"in a universe that's expanding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426862,"text":"What I do myself is to measure\nthe expansion of the universe,"},{"time":430189,"text":"and one of the projects\nthat I carried out in the 1990s"},{"time":433354,"text":"used the Hubble Space Telescope to measure\nhow fast the universe is expanding."},{"time":439356,"text":"We can now trace back to 14 billion years."},{"time":443731,"text":"We've learned over time\nthat stars have individual histories;"},{"time":448091,"text":"that is, they have birth,\nthey have middle ages"},{"time":451044,"text":"and some of them\neven have dramatic deaths."},{"time":453829,"text":"So the embers from those stars actually\nthen form the new stars that we see,"},{"time":459968,"text":"most of which turn out to have\nplanets going around them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464272,"text":"And one of the really surprising results\nin the last 20 years"},{"time":468331,"text":"has been the discovery\nof other planets going around other stars."},{"time":472481,"text":"These are called exoplanets."},{"time":474411,"text":"And until 1995, we didn't even know\nthe existence of any other planets,"},{"time":479431,"text":"other than going around our own sun."},{"time":482360,"text":"But now, there are almost 2,000\nother planets orbiting other stars"},{"time":488805,"text":"that we can now detect,\nmeasure masses for."},{"time":491389,"text":"There are 500 of those\nthat are multiple-planet systems."},{"time":495085,"text":"And there are 4,000 --\nand still counting -- other candidates"},{"time":499069,"text":"for planets orbiting other stars."},{"time":501790,"text":"They come in a bewildering variety\nof different kinds."},{"time":505134,"text":"There are Jupiter-like\nplanets that are hot,"},{"time":508444,"text":"there are other planets that are icy,\nthere are water worlds"},{"time":512726,"text":"and there are rocky planets\nlike the Earth, so-called \"super-Earths,\""},{"time":516004,"text":"and there have even been planets\nthat have been speculated diamond worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521794,"text":"So we know there's at least one planet,\nour own Earth, in which there is life."},{"time":526773,"text":"We've even found planets\nthat are orbiting two stars."},{"time":530957,"text":"That's no longer the province\nof science fiction."},{"time":535211,"text":"So around our own planet,\nwe know there's life,"},{"time":537449,"text":"we've developed a complex life,\nwe now can question our own origins."},{"time":543728,"text":"And given all that we've discovered,\nthe overwhelming numbers now suggest"},{"time":547972,"text":"that there may be millions, perhaps --\nmaybe even hundreds of millions --"},{"time":552068,"text":"of other [planets]\nthat are close enough --"},{"time":554871,"text":"just the right distance from their stars\nthat they're orbiting --"},{"time":558185,"text":"to have the existence of liquid water\nand maybe could potentially support life."},{"time":564121,"text":"So we marvel now at those odds,\nthe overwhelming odds,"},{"time":568319,"text":"and the amazing thing\nis that within the next decade,"},{"time":571286,"text":"the GMT may be able to take spectra\nof the atmospheres of those planets,"},{"time":576540,"text":"and determine whether or not\nthey have the potential for life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581702,"text":"So, what is the GMT project?"},{"time":583506,"text":"It's an international project."},{"time":585404,"text":"It includes Australia, South Korea,\nand I'm happy to say, being here in Rio,"},{"time":591277,"text":"that the newest partner\nin our telescope is Brazil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594825,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":599308,"text":"It also includes a number of institutions\nacross the United States,"},{"time":604122,"text":"including Harvard University,"},{"time":607242,"text":"the Smithsonian\nand the Carnegie Institutions,"},{"time":610210,"text":"and the Universities of Arizona, Chicago,\nTexas-Austin and Texas A&amp;M University."},{"time":617074,"text":"It also involves Chile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620723,"text":"So, the making of the mirrors\nin this telescope is also fascinating"},{"time":623959,"text":"in its own right."},{"time":625348,"text":"Take chunks of glass, melt them\nin a furnace that is itself rotating."},{"time":630751,"text":"This happens underneath\nthe football stadium"},{"time":632866,"text":"at the University of Arizona."},{"time":634932,"text":"It's tucked away under 52,000 seats."},{"time":637892,"text":"Nobody know it's happening."},{"time":639738,"text":"And there's essentially\na rotating cauldron."},{"time":643086,"text":"The mirrors are cast\nand they're cooled very slowly,"},{"time":646145,"text":"and then they're polished\nto an exquisite precision."},{"time":649637,"text":"And so, if you think\nabout the precision of these mirrors,"},{"time":652738,"text":"the bumps on the mirror,\nover the entire 27 feet,"},{"time":657315,"text":"amount to less\nthan one-millionth of an inch."},{"time":661018,"text":"So, can you visualize that?"},{"time":663089,"text":"Ow!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664264,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":665612,"text":"That's one five-thousandths\nof the width of one of my hairs,"},{"time":671907,"text":"over this entire 27 feet."},{"time":674068,"text":"It's a spectacular achievement."},{"time":675962,"text":"It's what allows us to have\nthe precision that we will have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680876,"text":"So, what does that precision buy us?"},{"time":683843,"text":"So the GMT, if you can imagine --"},{"time":686606,"text":"if I were to hold up a coin,\nwhich I just happen to have,"},{"time":691079,"text":"and I look at the face of that coin,\nI can see from here"},{"time":696094,"text":"the writing on the coin;\nI can see the face on that coin."},{"time":700103,"text":"My guess that even in the front row,\nyou can't see that."},{"time":703645,"text":"But if we were to turn\nthe Giant Magellan Telescope,"},{"time":706531,"text":"all 80-feet diameter\nthat we see in this auditorium,"},{"time":709928,"text":"and point it 200 miles away,"},{"time":713021,"text":"if I were standing in São Paulo,\nwe could resolve the face of this coin."},{"time":718913,"text":"That's the extraordinary resolution\nand power of this telescope."},{"time":723761,"text":"And if we were --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":726483,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":730377,"text":"If an astronaut went up to the Moon,\na quarter of a million miles away,"},{"time":735002,"text":"and lit a candle -- a single candle --"},{"time":737942,"text":"then we would be able\nto detect it, using the GMT."},{"time":741347,"text":"Quite extraordinary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745334,"text":"This is a simulated image\nof a cluster in a nearby galaxy."},{"time":751039,"text":"\"Nearby\" is astronomical,\nit's all relative."},{"time":753648,"text":"It's tens of millions of light-years away."},{"time":756175,"text":"This is what this cluster would look like."},{"time":758213,"text":"So look at those four bright objects,"},{"time":760405,"text":"and now lets compare it with a camera\non the Hubble Space Telescope."},{"time":764436,"text":"You can see faint detail\nthat starts to come through."},{"time":767639,"text":"And now finally -- and look how dramatic\nthis is -- this is what the GMT will see."},{"time":773958,"text":"So, keep your eyes on those\nbright images again."},{"time":776352,"text":"This is what we see on one of the most\npowerful existing telescopes on the Earth,"},{"time":780794,"text":"and this, again, what the GMT will see."},{"time":784554,"text":"Extraordinary precision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786975,"text":"So, where are we?"},{"time":788321,"text":"We have now leveled the top\nof the mountaintop in Chile."},{"time":791527,"text":"We blasted that off."},{"time":793314,"text":"We've tested and polished\nthe first mirror."},{"time":796057,"text":"We've cast the second\nand the third mirrors."},{"time":798670,"text":"And we're about to cast the fourth mirror."},{"time":800963,"text":"We had a series of reviews this year,"},{"time":802874,"text":"international panels\nthat came in and reviewed us,"},{"time":805440,"text":"and said, \"You're ready\nto go to construction.\""},{"time":807995,"text":"And so we plan on building this telescope\nwith the first four mirrors."},{"time":811368,"text":"We want to get on the air quickly,\nand be taking science data --"},{"time":815521,"text":"what we astronomers call\n\"first light,\" in 2021."},{"time":821031,"text":"And the full telescope will be finished\nin the middle of the next decade,"},{"time":824501,"text":"with all seven mirrors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826542,"text":"So we're now poised to look back\nat the distant universe,"},{"time":830124,"text":"the cosmic dawn."},{"time":831804,"text":"We'll be able to study other planets\nin exquisite detail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836424,"text":"But for me, one of the most\nexciting things about building the GMT"},{"time":840185,"text":"is the opportunity\nto actually discover something"},{"time":843039,"text":"that we don't know about --\nthat we can't even imagine at this point,"},{"time":846333,"text":"something completely new."},{"time":848713,"text":"And my hope is that with the construction\nof this and other facilities,"},{"time":852367,"text":"that many young women and men\nwill be inspired to reach for the stars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858036,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":859332,"text":"Obrigado."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860831,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":866748,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thank you, Wendy."},{"time":868374,"text":"Stay with me, because\nI have a question for you."},{"time":870665,"text":"You mentioned different facilities."},{"time":873086,"text":"So the Magellan Telescope is going up,\nbut also ALMA and others in Chile"},{"time":877963,"text":"and elsewhere, including in Hawaii."},{"time":880772,"text":"Is it about cooperation\nand complementarity, or about competition?"},{"time":884872,"text":"I know there's competition in terms\nof funding, but what about the science?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888618,"text":"Wendy Freedman: In terms of the science,\nthey're very complementary."},{"time":891859,"text":"The telescopes that are in space,\nthe telescopes on the ground,"},{"time":894910,"text":"telescopes with different\nwavelength capability,"},{"time":897364,"text":"telescopes even that are similar,\nbut different instruments --"},{"time":900331,"text":"they will all look at different parts\nof the questions that we're asking."},{"time":904101,"text":"So when we discover other planets,\nwe'll be able to test those observations,"},{"time":907752,"text":"we'll be able to measure the atmospheres,"},{"time":909864,"text":"be able to look in space\nwith very high resolution."},{"time":912763,"text":"So, they're very complementary."},{"time":914264,"text":"You're right about\nthe funding, we compete;"},{"time":916525,"text":"but scientifically,\nit's very complementary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":919214,"text":"BG: Wendy, thank you very much\nfor coming to TEDGlobal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921891,"text":"WF: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923066,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}